div.p:
This diagram follows the UML definition of data flow diagram. Follow it from down to top, for proofs going from the receipts up to the beacon chain. The height is significant on reading it, data from top is built from data in the bottom.
The dotted lines represent that data structure that you can get from the other data structure the dote line is pointed to. For example, beacon block ---> execution payload
The whole lines represent that the data is being transfered to a process that needs it to output a proof.
